From ffe3c0d461deb69bbb65543bf40bde53ee2006ff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joel Fernandes <joelagnelf@nvidia.com>
Date: Mon, 26 Jan 2026 10:59:01 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] sched/debug: Stop and start server based on if it was active

References: bsc#1234634 (Scheduler functional and performance backports SL-16.1)
Patch-mainline: v7.0-rc1
Git-commit: 68ec89d0e99156803bdea3c986c0198624e40ea2

Currently the DL server interface for applying parameters checks
CFS-internals to identify if the server is active. This is error-prone
and makes it difficult when adding new servers in the future.

Fix it, by using dl_server_active() which is also used by the DL server
code to determine if the DL server was started.

Signed-off-by: Joel Fernandes <joelagnelf@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
Reviewed-by: Juri Lelli <juri.lelli@redhat.com>
Reviewed-by: Andrea Righi <arighi@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Tejun Heo <tj@kernel.org>
Tested-by: Christian Loehle <christian.loehle@arm.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20260126100050.3854740-4-arighi@nvidia.com
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 kernel/sched/debug.c | 11 ++++++++---
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/debug.c b/kernel/sched/debug.c
index c6706bd86ca9..537b81a3eeb7 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/debug.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/debug.c
@@ -357,6 +357,8 @@ static ssize_t sched_fair_server_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *ubu
 		return err;
 
 	scoped_guard (rq_lock_irqsave, rq) {
+		bool is_active;
+
 		runtime  = rq->fair_server.dl_runtime;
 		period = rq->fair_server.dl_period;
 
@@ -379,8 +381,11 @@ static ssize_t sched_fair_server_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *ubu
 			return  -EINVAL;
 		}
 
-		update_rq_clock(rq);
-		dl_server_stop(&rq->fair_server);
+		is_active = dl_server_active(&rq->fair_server);
+		if (is_active) {
+			update_rq_clock(rq);
+			dl_server_stop(&rq->fair_server);
+		}
 
 		retval = dl_server_apply_params(&rq->fair_server, runtime, period, 0);
 
@@ -388,7 +393,7 @@ static ssize_t sched_fair_server_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *ubu
 			printk_deferred("Fair server disabled in CPU %d, system may crash due to starvation.\n",
 					cpu_of(rq));
 
-		if (rq->cfs.h_nr_queued)
+		if (is_active && runtime)
 			dl_server_start(&rq->fair_server);
 
 		if (retval < 0)
